## Stimulus Controllers

Stimulus adds JavaScript behavior to HTML elements.

### Basic Stimulus Controller

```javascript
// app/javascript/controllers/dropdown_controller.js

import { Controller } from "@hotwired/stimulus"

// Connects to data-controller="dropdown"
export default class extends Controller {
  // Define targets (elements to reference)
  static targets = ["menu", "button"]
  
  // Define CSS classes (for dynamic styling)
  static classes = ["open", "closed"]
  
  // Define values (dynamic data from HTML)
  static values = {
    openDuration: { type: Number, default: 300 }
  }
  
  // Lifecycle: runs when controller connects to DOM
  connect() {
    this.close()
  }
  
  // Lifecycle: runs when controller disconnects
  disconnect() {
    // Cleanup if needed
  }
  
  // Actions (called from HTML via data-action)
  toggle(event) {
    event.preventDefault()
    this.isOpen ? this.close() : this.open()
  }
  
  open() {
    this.menuTarget.classList.remove(this.closedClass)
    this.menuTarget.classList.add(this.openClass)
    this.buttonTarget.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true')
  }
  
  close() {
    this.menuTarget.classList.add(this.closedClass)
    this.menuTarget.classList.remove(this.openClass)
    this.buttonTarget.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false')
  }
  
  // Close when clicking outside
  closeOnClickOutside(event) {
    if (!this.element.contains(event.target)) {
      this.close()
    }
  }
  
  // Helper methods
  get isOpen() {
    return this.menuTarget.classList.contains(this.openClass)
  }
}
```

### HTML Usage

```html
<div data-controller="dropdown"
     data-action="click@window->dropdown#closeOnClickOutside"
     data-dropdown-open-class="block"
     data-dropdown-closed-class="hidden"
     id="user-menu-dropdown-container">
  
  <button data-action="click->dropdown#toggle"
          data-dropdown-target="button"
          id="user-menu-toggle-button"
          aria-haspopup="true"
          aria-expanded="false">
    Menu
  </button>
  
  <div data-dropdown-target="menu"
       class="hidden"
       id="user-menu-dropdown-menu">
    <a href="/profile">Profile</a>
    <a href="/settings">Settings</a>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Stimulus Targets

```javascript
// Define targets in controller
static targets = ["input", "output", "button"]

// Access targets in methods
this.inputTarget          // First matching element
this.inputTargets         // Array of all matching elements
this.hasInputTarget       // Boolean: does target exist?

// Multiple targets example
static targets = ["item"]

addItem() {
  // Access all items
  this.itemTargets.forEach(item => {
    item.classList.add('selected')
  })
}
```

### Stimulus Values

```javascript
// Define values with types and defaults
static values = {
  url: String,
  delay: { type: Number, default: 300 },
  enabled: { type: Boolean, default: true }
}

// Access values in methods
this.urlValue              // Get value
this.urlValue = "/new"     // Set value
this.hasUrlValue           // Boolean: is value set?

// Value change callbacks
urlValueChanged(value, previousValue) {
  console.log(`URL changed from ${previousValue} to ${value}`)
}
```

### Stimulus Classes

```javascript
// Define CSS class names
static classes = ["active", "loading", "error"]

// Use in methods
this.element.classList.add(this.activeClass)
this.element.classList.remove(this.loadingClass)

// Check if class is defined
if (this.hasActiveClass) {
  this.element.classList.add(this.activeClass)
}
